article.headline: Marist 89, Bucknell 63
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Ryan Schneider had 29 points, nine rebounds and five steals to lead Marist over Bucknell 89-63 Sunday. Dejuan Goodwin added 16 points for the Red Foxes (5-8), while Javon Parris scored 15. Schneider, who shot 13-for-19, hit a three-pointer with with 8:41 left in the first half for the 15-13 lead, and Marist stayed ahead after that. The Red Foxes closed the first half with an 11-2 run. They put the game out of reach with a 16-1 run in the second half in which Schneider scored eight. G.W. Boon scored 14 points off the bench for Bucknell (3-8), while Bryan Cohen had 11.
